    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-08-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-08-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="49"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d49">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/2000: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Bolivian Minister for Foreign Affairs (<persName
                            corresp="#p_GJA1" type="from">Gutiérrez</persName>) to the Assistant
                        Secretary of State (<persName corresp="#p_WF1" type="to"
                        >White</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-09">August 9,
                            1932</date>.<lb/>[Received 9:13 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Supplementing note of yesterday relative to temporary suspension of hostilities
                    we should like to be informed specifically whether neutral mediators and
                    Paraguay agree to our proposal basis present possessions to maintain on our part
                    suspension hostilities.</p>
                <p>Sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Julio A. Gutiérrez</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
